- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with game theory and optimal strategies in games.
- cs.LO (Computer Science and Logic) is also likely as the paper involves formal frameworks and characterizations of preference relations.
- cs.DS (Computer Science and Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper discusses memory requirements and strategies in games, which can be seen as algorithmic problems.
- cs.AI (Computer Science and Artificial Intelligence) is another possibility as the paper deals with controller synthesis and finding optimal strategies, which are common problems in AI.
- cs.PL (Computer Science and Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper involves formal languages and specifications.
